      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "canned"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in the pressure cooker over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it is translucent and starting to brown.",
    "Add the ground lamb and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until it is no longer pink.",
    "Add the chopped carrots and potatoes, dried bay leaf, paprika, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the lamb broth and tomato paste, and stir to combine.",
    "Close the lid of the pressure cooker and bring to high pressure.",
    "Cook for 20 minutes, then allow the pressure to release naturally.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley or thyme, if desired."
  ],
